35:16.375 --> 35:17.158
Where?

35:17.289 --> 35:18.812
<i>Patch Café.</i>

35:18.986 --> 35:20.553
How far from the Hilton?

35:20.770 --> 35:23.164
Everything in Midland's
15 minutes from everything else.

35:23.338 --> 35:24.383
I'll meet you there.

35:24.557 --> 35:26.472
<i>All right.</i>

35:26.689 --> 35:28.604
<i>♪ "Mean Old Sun"
by Turnpike Troubadours ♪</i>

35:28.778 --> 35:32.130
<i>♪ Empty promises ♪</i>

35:32.260 --> 35:35.263
<i>♪ I've given ♪</i>

35:35.437 --> 35:37.396
<i>♪ Hollow heart ♪</i>

35:37.526 --> 35:39.267
<i>♪ Beats in my chest ♪</i>

35:40.921 --> 35:43.663
<i>♪ And every word ♪</i>

35:43.837 --> 35:46.535
<i>♪ Of sterling silver ♪</i>

35:46.753 --> 35:50.670
<i>♪ Stirred butterflies
beneath your breast... ♪</i>

35:50.844 --> 35:52.062
[car alarm chirps]

35:53.020 --> 35:55.544
<i>♪ Still untouched ♪</i>

35:55.762 --> 35:58.721
<i>♪ By ties a-binding ♪</i>

35:58.895 --> 36:01.985
<i>♪ Going where ♪</i>

36:02.160 --> 36:04.901
<i>♪ The gulf breeze blows ♪</i>

36:05.075 --> 36:08.035
<i>♪ No ring of gold ♪</i>

36:08.209 --> 36:11.038
<i>♪ Around your finger ♪</i>

36:11.212 --> 36:14.259
<i>♪ No ring of brass ♪</i>

36:14.433 --> 36:16.739
<i>♪ Run through my nose ♪</i>

36:18.350 --> 36:19.351
<i>♪ Headlong for... ♪</i>

36:19.525 --> 36:21.788
Hi, I'm here to see
a Tommy Norris.

36:22.005 --> 36:24.094
[hostess]
Cowboy hat at the bar.

36:24.225 --> 36:26.923
<i>♪ Dead still in the garden ♪</i>

36:27.097 --> 36:30.275
<i>♪ Waiting for the reveille ♪</i>

36:30.449 --> 36:33.147
<i>♪ And the dawn has yet
to dry the dew ♪</i>

36:33.365 --> 36:36.194
<i>♪ From off my Sunday clothes ♪</i>

36:36.368 --> 36:39.022
<i>♪ That mean old sun
better rise up soon ♪</i>

36:39.153 --> 36:41.677
<i>♪ If it's ever gonna set on me ♪</i>

36:43.201 --> 36:45.942
<i>♪ Hear the song ♪</i>

36:46.116 --> 36:49.250
<i>♪ She sang in darkness ♪</i>

36:49.424 --> 36:50.904
<i>♪ Tearful, fair... ♪</i>

36:51.078 --> 36:52.558
I'm that easy to spot, huh?

36:52.732 --> 36:54.516
Wasn't difficult.

36:54.690 --> 36:55.952
- You want a drink?
- Yeah.

36:56.126 --> 36:57.519
A club soda.

36:57.693 --> 36:59.304
Hey, bud?
Club soda for the lady.

36:59.478 --> 37:00.783
[Barney]
Just so you know,

37:00.957 --> 37:02.829
that is a nonalcoholic drink.

37:02.959 --> 37:04.787
This must be your hobby

37:05.005 --> 37:06.833
'cause you damn sure
don't want a fucking tip.

37:07.050 --> 37:10.402
I'd prefer if you didn't
refer to me as "the lady."

37:11.533 --> 37:12.926
Oh, did I guess wrong?

37:13.100 --> 37:14.797
I'm so sorry, sir,

37:14.971 --> 37:16.364
and hats off
to the plastic surgeon

37:16.538 --> 37:18.148
that shaved that Adam's apple.

37:18.279 --> 37:19.628
My first day in the oil fields,

37:19.846 --> 37:21.108
and it doesn't disappoint.

37:21.282 --> 37:23.153
It is as offensive
as I imagined.

37:23.328 --> 37:25.808
You know the sharks
you work with?

37:25.982 --> 37:28.289
You soulless fucks represent

37:28.507 --> 37:30.422
the Bin Laden family,
for Christ's sakes.

37:30.639 --> 37:33.425
You should be thanking me
for calling you "lady."

37:33.599 --> 37:35.383
You may never hear it again
in your line of work.

37:37.951 --> 37:40.301
I'm sorry,
but I lost three friends

37:40.432 --> 37:42.172
and a finger today, so...

37:42.347 --> 37:43.261
I'm a little edgy.

37:43.391 --> 37:45.437
I didn't know they were friends.

37:46.742 --> 37:48.135
They were friends.

37:48.309 --> 37:49.832
I'm sorry.

37:52.444 --> 37:55.316
We need to shift our focus
from TTP

37:55.490 --> 37:57.231
to the incident this morning.

37:57.405 --> 37:58.885
It lends itself
to more exposure.

38:00.582 --> 38:02.062
You're the attorney.

38:02.280 --> 38:04.238
Can you take me
to the incident site tomorrow?

38:04.456 --> 38:05.892
I can take you right now.

38:06.022 --> 38:07.937
Great.

38:08.111 --> 38:09.852
- All right.
- Let's go.

38:10.070 --> 38:11.376
- [Tommy] Hey, bud?
- [Barney] Mm-hmm.

38:11.550 --> 38:12.986
- Let me take care of this.
- Yep.

38:14.770 --> 38:16.729
You want change?

38:16.903 --> 38:17.991
I can't believe you said that
with a straight face.

38:18.165 --> 38:19.427
Of course I want fucking change.

38:28.480 --> 38:30.220
<i>♪ dramatic music ♪</i>

38:30.656 --> 38:32.484
<i>♪</i>

38:49.718 --> 38:52.112
Sorry about the dust.

38:52.286 --> 38:54.157
[Rebecca]
It's a rental.

38:54.332 --> 38:56.421
So, who besides
insurance companies

38:56.551 --> 38:58.553
and county sheriff
investigate this?

38:58.727 --> 39:01.339
Hell, everybody. OSHA,
Railroad Commission, DPS.

39:01.469 --> 39:03.036
Shouldn't you know all this shit

39:03.210 --> 39:05.691
if you're litigating
a petroleum liability case?

39:05.865 --> 39:07.649
My specialty
is chain of liability,

39:07.823 --> 39:09.434
which applies to the TTP case.

39:10.870 --> 39:13.351
Not so much here.

39:13.525 --> 39:15.614
This happened
when I was on the plane.

39:15.744 --> 39:17.442
Maybe they should send
another attorney.

39:20.532 --> 39:21.881
I understand
one of them survived.

39:22.098 --> 39:23.752
Yeah.

39:23.970 --> 39:25.188
Can I speak with him?

39:25.319 --> 39:26.755
- Not today.
- When?

39:26.929 --> 39:28.670
How about when he gets out
of the fucking hospital?

39:28.844 --> 39:30.542
Anything else?

39:34.241 --> 39:35.460
What can you tell from this?

39:37.331 --> 39:39.202
From the well? Nothing.

39:39.333 --> 39:41.074
From the type of fire?

39:41.248 --> 39:42.380
There was a leak.

39:42.510 --> 39:44.294
A roughneck created a spark

39:44.425 --> 39:46.601
when he tried to open the valve
with a hammer and a wrench.

39:46.819 --> 39:48.037
Why would he try to open it
with a hammer?

39:48.168 --> 39:49.430
'Cause that's how you open
the fucking thing.

39:49.604 --> 39:51.301
Doesn't seem very safe.

39:51.432 --> 39:54.217
It's not very safe. That's why
they make 180 grand a year.

39:54.392 --> 39:57.090
That's not enough money
to risk your life on.

39:57.220 --> 39:58.657
[chuckles]
Yeah, for you, maybe.

39:58.831 --> 40:00.441
For a felon with
an eighth-grade education,

40:00.615 --> 40:02.095
it's a fucking lottery ticket.

40:02.269 --> 40:03.879
And for an oil company
whose manager

40:04.010 --> 40:06.316
knowingly sends employees
to faulty wells

40:06.491 --> 40:08.406
that violate OSHA standards,

40:08.536 --> 40:09.885
it's a nine-figure lawsuit.

40:10.059 --> 40:12.540
Well, then the whole
goddamn industry's guilty.

40:19.155 --> 40:21.723
I'm on your side, Tommy.

40:22.985 --> 40:24.683
You need to understand that.

40:24.813 --> 40:25.988
Yeah, I understand plenty.

40:26.206 --> 40:29.644
You're the farthest thing
from being on my side.

40:40.263 --> 40:42.570
[truck engine starts]

41:06.899 --> 41:10.685
Son of a bitch. Son of a bitch.

41:18.476 --> 41:21.043
[Sellers]
<i>Information, education,</i>

41:21.261 --> 41:24.438
<i>and imagination are the weapons
against the assault</i>

41:24.656 --> 41:26.309
on oil and natural gas.

41:28.050 --> 41:30.531
But the weapon
being used against us

41:30.705 --> 41:31.924
is far more dangerous.

41:33.142 --> 41:35.014
Emotion.

41:35.188 --> 41:37.320
Emotion is the spear
of the green movement.

41:37.495 --> 41:39.018
[Cami] How did you rope me
into this in the first place?

41:39.192 --> 41:40.367
Wasn't this a...?
This was a date?

41:40.498 --> 41:41.499
- Come on, babe. It is a date.
- Mm-hmm.

41:41.716 --> 41:42.195
It's just the beginning
of a date.

41:42.369 --> 41:43.457
- Oh.
- The end of the date

41:43.675 --> 41:44.545
is when the date gets fun,
you know that.

41:44.719 --> 41:45.894
It better.

41:46.112 --> 41:47.374
[Sellers]
Mainstream media has abandoned

41:47.548 --> 41:48.680
evidence supporting facts

41:48.854 --> 41:50.899
in their panic
to prevent the exodus

41:51.117 --> 41:53.249
of their audience
to Twitter and TikTok

41:53.467 --> 41:55.164
as reliable news sources.

41:55.295 --> 41:56.252
- [phone buzzing]
- And that's before Russia...

41:56.426 --> 41:57.732
- Shit.
- ...China,

41:57.863 --> 41:59.038
- Iran, Hezbollah...
- Do you need to get that?

41:59.212 --> 42:00.692
- ...Hamas, Al-Qaeda...
- No, I'm not sure.

42:00.866 --> 42:02.041
...all of them
flooding social media...

42:02.215 --> 42:03.216
I feel like
I'm about to find out.

42:03.390 --> 42:04.609
[Sellers]
...with propaganda masquerading

42:04.739 --> 42:06.872
- as fear of climate change.
- [phone chimes]

42:07.089 --> 42:09.831
Yep. I do think
I have to get this.

42:10.005 --> 42:11.441
[Cami]
Okay.

42:11.616 --> 42:12.747
- [phone buzzing]
- Will you save my seat?

42:12.878 --> 42:14.967
Depends on how long you're gone.

42:15.141 --> 42:16.490
[Sellers] ...in arguably
the most uneducated populace...

42:16.664 --> 42:18.971
Hey. Let me call you right back.

42:19.101 --> 42:20.189
Yeah, I got to find
someplace quiet.

42:20.363 --> 42:22.278
<i>♪ dramatic music ♪</i>

42:22.714 --> 42:24.672
<i>♪</i>

42:53.179 --> 42:54.702
<i>♪</i>

43:01.317 --> 43:03.493
[line rings]

43:03.624 --> 43:05.278
- [Tommy over phone] <i>Yeah?</i>
- What is it?

43:05.452 --> 43:06.540
<i>The fuck do you think it is?</i>

43:06.758 --> 43:08.890
Who is this employee relations
pit viper

43:09.064 --> 43:10.022
you sent out here to bite me?

43:10.152 --> 43:12.938
Uh, I called Chandler
like you said.

43:13.112 --> 43:14.330
<i>Well, they didn't
fucking send him!</i>

43:14.504 --> 43:16.768
They sent somebody out here
to hang me out.

43:16.942 --> 43:20.032
<i>You don't have a well that
will pass OSHA standards, Monty.</i>

43:20.206 --> 43:21.555
<i>Not fucking one.</i>

43:21.773 --> 43:23.513
I'm a lot of shit, Monty,

43:23.688 --> 43:26.212
but I ain't a fucking patsy,
you understand me?

43:26.342 --> 43:27.300
<i>I called Clay,</i>

43:27.517 --> 43:29.171
who said he was flying to you.

43:29.389 --> 43:30.651
Now, I don't know who they sent
that isn't Clay,

43:30.825 --> 43:31.696
but I will find out.

43:31.913 --> 43:32.914
Good.

43:33.088 --> 43:34.350
<i>Now, look,</i>

43:34.524 --> 43:36.309
our business
is one of constant crisis

43:36.483 --> 43:39.138
interrupted by brief periods
of intense success.

43:39.312 --> 43:40.748
You should know that
better than anyone else.

43:41.749 --> 43:43.229
<i>Now, today was a rough one.</i>

43:43.446 --> 43:44.622
<i>And I can understand
why you might be emotional,</i>

43:44.752 --> 43:46.058
but don't let your emotions

43:46.188 --> 43:47.450
confuse you as to who
the boss is.

43:47.581 --> 43:49.191
The boss is me,

43:49.409 --> 43:51.803
and don't you ever raise
your fucking voice at me again.

43:52.238 --> 43:53.805
<i>♪</i>

44:08.341 --> 44:09.951
[phone buzzing]

44:12.562 --> 44:13.781
I'm on the way home, honey.

44:13.955 --> 44:15.914
[Ainsley]
<i>Yeah, I'm starving.</i>[groans]

44:16.131 --> 44:17.263
Like not, "I'm so hungry,
I feel like I'm starving."

44:17.393 --> 44:18.786
I'm starving.

44:19.004 --> 44:21.397
<i>Like, my skin looks pale,</i>

44:21.571 --> 44:23.443
- my organs are shutting down.
<i>- Well, there's</i>

44:23.617 --> 44:25.184
a kitchen full of food
in there, honey.

44:25.358 --> 44:28.056
<i>Daddy, there's a kitchen full
of processed cancer bombs.</i>

44:28.274 --> 44:30.232
And who orders Doritos
by the palette?

44:30.363 --> 44:31.886
I need protein.

44:32.017 --> 44:34.149
There's protein in the cupboard.

44:34.280 --> 44:36.108
Vienna sausages is not protein,
Daddy.

44:36.238 --> 44:37.762
You know,
it's all the parts of a cow

44:37.892 --> 44:39.546
that are too gross
to be in hot dogs.

44:39.677 --> 44:41.461
<i>Well, it's pork, but I'm not
gonna have that fight.</i>

44:41.679 --> 44:43.332
You want me
to pick you something up?

44:43.506 --> 44:48.120
Could you get me an animal-style
Whataburger wrapped in lettuce?

44:48.250 --> 44:49.774
<i>An animal what?</i>

44:49.948 --> 44:51.689
[clicks tongue]
It's, like, special sauce.

44:51.863 --> 44:54.082
And there's no bun.
They, like, wrap it in lettuce.

44:54.256 --> 44:55.823
How can they wrap it in lettuce?
Their lettuce is shredded.

44:55.997 --> 44:57.695
<i>Well, they always do it
when I ask.</i>

44:57.912 --> 44:59.784
They just go in the back,
and they get the whole lettuce.

44:59.914 --> 45:01.307
[chuckling] You and I live
in different worlds.

45:01.481 --> 45:03.004
They'll tell me to fuck myself.

45:03.178 --> 45:04.440
Why don't I just
get you a burger,

45:04.614 --> 45:06.486
and you throw the buns away?

45:06.704 --> 45:09.228
<i>Yeah. Yeah,
I guess we could do that.</i>

45:09.402 --> 45:11.056
And could you get me three fries
and a Diet Coke?

45:11.230 --> 45:12.579
<i>So,</i>

45:12.710 --> 45:14.799
you won't eat the buns,
but you'll eat three orders

45:14.973 --> 45:16.452
- of fries?
<i>- No!</i>

45:16.626 --> 45:18.628
I want three fries.
You have to pick out three,

45:18.759 --> 45:20.152
and then throw the rest
of them away.

45:21.501 --> 45:23.938
Okay. Anything else?

45:24.069 --> 45:25.461
<i>Thank you, Daddy.</i>

45:25.635 --> 45:27.637
Are you close?

45:27.812 --> 45:30.423
<i>No, and this is gonna add
ten minutes to the trip, too.</i>

45:30.597 --> 45:31.772
So, like, 15?

45:31.903 --> 45:32.991
<i>Like, an hour.</i>

45:33.165 --> 45:35.689
An hour?!

45:35.907 --> 45:37.430
I hope I'm still alive.

45:37.604 --> 45:38.910
<i>Well,</i>

45:39.127 --> 45:40.433
these are the challenges
that harden you

45:40.607 --> 45:42.043
for life's tragedies, honey.

45:42.217 --> 45:43.175
I'll see you soon.

45:43.349 --> 45:45.438
[groans]

45:45.612 --> 45:46.918
Okay, thank you. I love you.

45:47.092 --> 45:48.528
<i>Okay, love you, too, honey.</i>

45:48.702 --> 45:49.355
- I'll be there soon.
<i>- Will you hurry?</i>

45:49.485 --> 45:50.269
Yeah, I'll hurry.

45:50.486 --> 45:51.923
<i>Okay. Love you. Bye.</i>

45:52.140 --> 45:53.794
- Love you. Bye.
- [phone clicks]

45:53.968 --> 45:55.448
- [sinister ringtone playing]
- Goddamn!

45:55.665 --> 45:56.754
Shit.

45:56.884 --> 45:58.233
<i>Where you headed?</i>

45:58.407 --> 46:00.540
To the strip club.

46:00.758 --> 46:01.889
<i>While our daughter's there?</i>

46:02.107 --> 46:03.456
Yeah, she's meeting me there.

46:03.630 --> 46:05.763
I thought it's time she sees
the darker side of life.

46:05.893 --> 46:08.113
<i>Where are you really headed?</i>

46:08.330 --> 46:09.897
I'm going home.

46:11.246 --> 46:12.378
<i>You look tired.</i>

46:12.508 --> 46:14.510
There's a reason for that.

46:14.684 --> 46:16.382
<i>I don't really need to come.</i>

46:16.556 --> 46:18.340
<i>Do I need to come?</i>

46:18.514 --> 46:20.821
I already told you
you don't need to come.

46:20.952 --> 46:23.389
<i>What if I want to come?</i>

46:23.563 --> 46:24.694
Why would you want to do that?

46:24.912 --> 46:26.696
<i>What if I did?</i>

46:26.871 --> 46:29.612
You want to leave Cabo
and come to Midland, Texas

46:29.830 --> 46:32.137
to fuck your ex-husband in a
rent house with three roommates?

46:32.354 --> 46:33.965
Why do I doubt that?

46:34.139 --> 46:36.489
<i>Can't you just fucking want me
to come?</i>

46:36.619 --> 46:37.925
<i>Why can't you do that?</i>

46:38.099 --> 46:41.189
Oh, honey, I want you to come,
believe me.

46:41.363 --> 46:43.931
[chuckles] I mean,
I just know you'll never do it.

46:44.105 --> 46:46.194
Breaks my heart.
I really want you to.

46:46.368 --> 46:48.501
<i>You'll think about it later,
I bet.</i>

46:48.631 --> 46:50.155
Well, since I'm sharing a bed
with our daughter,

46:50.372 --> 46:52.287
I hope
I don't think about it later.

46:53.593 --> 46:55.508
<i>- I'll call you tomorrow.
- ♪ slow, melancholy music</i>

46:55.682 --> 46:57.336
Okay. Good night, Angie.

46:57.510 --> 46:59.904
<i>Mm-hmm. Good night.</i>

47:08.651 --> 47:10.349
<i>♪ slow, gentle music ♪</i>

47:10.784 --> 47:14.005
<i>♪</i>

47:41.641 --> 47:43.295
[door closes]

47:49.344 --> 47:50.911
[Ainsley]
[sighs] Thank you, God.

47:51.042 --> 47:53.000
There you go.

47:55.437 --> 47:58.266
[sighs] I talked them into
the lettuce thing in back there.

47:59.615 --> 48:01.400
- How'd you do that?
- Showed 'em your picture.

48:01.574 --> 48:02.836
[both chuckle]

48:05.186 --> 48:07.885
Daddy, I said three fries.
There's a whole order in here.

48:08.059 --> 48:09.582
- Well, the rest are for me.
- Well,

48:09.712 --> 48:10.670
I'm just gonna
talk you out of them, Daddy.

48:10.844 --> 48:11.540
You need to throw 'em away.

48:11.714 --> 48:14.021
Now. Now!

48:18.678 --> 48:20.506
You know, this shit was cute
when you were eight,

48:20.680 --> 48:23.683
but now all I think about's
your first marriage

48:23.857 --> 48:25.641
and the skid marks
that poor bastard leaves

48:25.815 --> 48:27.382
after he's had a few years
of this shit.

48:27.556 --> 48:29.863
It annoys you
because you're my father,

48:30.037 --> 48:32.474
and you don't want
to have sex with me.

48:32.648 --> 48:34.607
But other boys look
at these chores like...

48:34.781 --> 48:36.087
little treasure hunts.

48:38.524 --> 48:41.179
Oh, your brother's in the
hospital. I forgot to tell you.

48:41.353 --> 48:43.137
- Sorry about that.
- Where?

48:43.268 --> 48:44.878
Here.

48:45.052 --> 48:47.185
- What's he doing in Midland?
- Working for me.

48:47.315 --> 48:49.709
But he doesn't graduate
till May.

48:49.883 --> 48:52.190
He don't graduate ever.
He dropped out.

48:52.364 --> 48:53.582
He wants to work in the patch.

48:54.627 --> 48:56.846
He is such a loser.

49:00.720 --> 49:02.504
Daddy, I didn't...
I didn't mean it like that.

49:03.810 --> 49:05.594
Let me tell you something, honey.

49:07.509 --> 49:09.468
There's two types of people
that work in the patch--

49:09.642 --> 49:11.252
dreamers and losers.

49:13.559 --> 49:15.343
Used to be that way
in the whole nation.

49:17.650 --> 49:22.089
Failures headed out West
to either die or succeed.

49:23.917 --> 49:25.049
All the way to California.

49:27.312 --> 49:29.488
But there's not any dreamers
out there anymore,

49:29.705 --> 49:32.099
just thieves and fools.

49:33.840 --> 49:36.147
This is where dreamers come now.

49:38.453 --> 49:40.281
And losers come here to win.

49:44.329 --> 49:46.331
Which one are you gonna be?

49:49.247 --> 49:51.118
A dreamer.

49:51.292 --> 49:53.425
First attempt's
always a failure,

49:53.555 --> 49:55.340
so it means
you're gonna be a loser.

49:56.515 --> 49:59.126
Wonder what you'll do then.

50:05.132 --> 50:08.179
You take my room tonight,
and I'll, uh, take the couch.

